<!--
  ============================================================
  PINT-AE 1.0.3 — Disclosed Agent Billing
  ============================================================
  Scenario  : Travel management company (TMC) "Horizon Travel
              Services LLC" acts as a disclosed agent on behalf
              of corporate client "Gulf Dynamics FZE".
              TMC books airline tickets and hotel from Emirates
              Airlines and Rotana Hotels and raises a single
              consolidated invoice to the client, clearly
              disclosing that it is acting as agent.
              Under UAE VAT, the supply is treated as made
              directly by the principal (Emirates / Rotana) to
              the client; the agent's commission is a separate
              supply. Both are captured here per PINT-AE rules.
  Supplier  : Horizon Travel Services LLC (Disclosed Agent)
  Buyer     : Gulf Dynamics FZE (Corporate Client / Principal)
  VAT       : Standard rated (S) 5%
              Net supply value = AED 18,500.00
              Agent commission  = AED 1,500.00
              Total net         = AED 20,000.00
              VAT (5%)          = AED 1,000.00
              Total payable     = AED 21,000.00
  Currency  : AED
  Legal ref : UAE Federal Decree-Law No.8/2017 Art. 9
              UAE VAT Executive Regulations Art. 45
              — Supplies made through agents
  ============================================================
  ProfileExecutionID bitmap (8 digits):
  Pos 1: Free Trade Zone       → 0
  Pos 2: Deemed Supply         → 0
  Pos 3: Profit Margin Scheme  → 0
  Pos 4: Summary Invoice       → 0
  Pos 5: Continuous Supply     → 0
  Pos 6: Disclosed Agent Billing → 1  ← this invoice
  Pos 7: Supply via e-commerce → 0
  Pos 8: Exports               → 0
  Result → 00000100
  ============================================================
-->
